# Peaks transient/per-session state (regenerable, not shared knowledge).
# Layout (as of slice 2026-06-05-change-id-as-unit-of-work):
#   .peaks/_runtime/                ← all ephemeral runtime state
#                                       (active-skill, session binding,
#                                        current-change symlink/file)
#   .peaks/[0-9]*-session-*/        ← session dirs (ephemeral scratch;
#                                       contain only system/ sub-agent state)
#   .peaks/memory/                  ← durable project memory (tracked; knowledge base)
#   .peaks/sops/                    ← durable SOP definitions (tracked; shared with team)
#   .peaks/PROJECT.md               ← durable project timeline (tracked)
#   .peaks/.peaks-init-hooks-decision.json ← durable install decision (tracked)
#   .peaks/<change-id>/             ← durable change-id artifacts (tracked;
#                                       cross-session accumulation of the
#                                       unit of work — RD/QA/PRD/txt)
#   .peaks/session.json             ← legacy top-level binding (gitignored;
#                                       canonical moved to _runtime/session.json)
.peaks/**/.bypass-count.json
.peaks/ontology.json
# Per-slice session directories — these are session-scoped, regenerable, and
# large. The gitignore rule below covers both the legacy top-level
# `.peaks/<session-id>/` and the new canonical `.peaks/_runtime/<session-id>/`.
.peaks/_runtime/
.peaks/[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-session-*/
# Legacy top-level binding (one-minor-release back-compat; canonical home is _runtime/session.json).
.peaks/session.json
# Test / debug backups left by sub-agent baselines (e.g. .peaks/.active-skill.json.test-bak from QA's git-stash verification)
.peaks/*.bak
.peaks/*.test-bak
.peaks/**/*.bak
.peaks/**/*.test-bak
# Tracked content that lives at the top level of .peaks/ (NOT ignored):
#   - .peaks/memory/                       (durable project knowledge)
#   - .peaks/sops/                         (durable SOP definitions)
#   - .peaks/PROJECT.md                    (durable session timeline)
#   - .peaks/.peaks-init-hooks-decision.json (first-run opt-in marker)
#   - .peaks/<change-id>/                  (durable change-id scoped artifacts;
#                                            reviewable across sessions)
